@anchor{filters first}@anchor{40}
@subsection first


Returns the first item in a list.

For example:

@example
@{@{ value|first @}@}
@end example

If @code{value} is the list @code{("a" "b" "c")}, the output will be @code{"a"}.

@node join,last,first,List of filters
@anchor{filters join}@anchor{41}
@subsection join


Joins a list with a string.

For example:

@example
@{@{ value|join:" // " @}@}
@end example

If @code{value} is the list @code{("a" "b" "c")}, the output will be the string
@code{"a // b // c"}.

